reviews.text:
Pay attention to local parking - unfair practices !!! Penalty notice even if everything is in order! SABA is very, very unfair in this case. 
Avoid this unfair business!!!

We were caught up in yesterdays power failures. Finsbury park station ticket office need to hang their head in shame, they were rude and when I asked for advice the man there said you are on your own all of you. We got to Potters Bar and the man and young lady there had everything sorted for people, buses laid on and Taxis. The young lady was between 18 and 22ish but she is a real credit to your rail service. We had already rang for our local company to come from Peterborough to get us but I do believe she would have sorted something for us
my least fav train station sorry
I came back to my car and could not get in using any of the doors due to cars parked so close both sides. My car was central to my parking space. The office do not want to help
A slow sighing blueness, a piano's lament
